                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/3584.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-12T21:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 12, 1912—9 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Aguascalientes reports revolutionists held up train from Guanajuato to Silao and
                    American conductor (name not given) was fatally <pb facs="1037" n="921"
                        xml:id="pg_921"/> shot; all passengers and employees maltreated. Also
                    reports wrecking of train at Trapuato and killing of American engineer,
                    Zachariah Farmer.</p>
                <p>I am to-day advised by the representatives of American railway servants on
                    Mexican National Railways that they would go out in a body on April 17. I
                    believe efforts to save the situation Avill be unavailing. The said
                    representatives have expressed to me their deep appreciation of the sympathetic
                    attitude of this Embassy and of the Washington Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
